      <div class="msgContentFrame">I've been reading forum posts, blog posts, watching videos on YouTube, etc. <br /> <br />I think the main beef people have, when they complain about the challenge in Beta Heroics, isn't that it is challenging, it is more like the step up is absolutely ridiculous. <br /> <br />You go from questing, where you could nearly fall asleep (let's use cold water as an analogy), and your character never dies, to 5-man normals, which are 'so-so', you'll die if you do things wrong, but for most intents and purposes, you shouldn't be dying if your group has half a clue (lukewarm water) to Heroics.... <br /> <br />Heroics, you must have everything right, and even when you do, you barely win by the skin of your teeth. Basically, you're going from Cold Water, Lukewarm Water to Boiling Hot Water. <br /> <br />I wouldn't mind challenging Heroics, but I think they could smooth the curve out a bit. I mean, healers going OOM in 30 seconds, the tank getting killed in &lt;5 seconds? I thought they said they wanted damage to be <i>less</i> spiky instead of <i>more</i>? <br /> <br />It is like a staircase... <br /> <br />From the ground to the first step is about 6 inches. <br />From the first step to the second is another 6 inches. <br />From the second step to the third is two feet. <br /> <br />Something just doesn't look right there. I know they wanted the heroics to be a little more challenging than Wrath's (and I agree), but I don't think they need to be Hard-Mode Raid hard, either. I don't think we need Algalon25 or Yogg+0 in every stinking 5-man.</div>
      <div class="msgFtFrame"><div class="msgFtFrameFix"></div><div class="msgReplies"><a href="javascript:scrollTo(0,0);">&#9650; Page top</a> |   <a href="/forum.html?forum=21&amp;mid=128602454531215128&amp;page=1&amp;howmany=50#msg128602538341686235" class="icon-linktothis" rel="nofollow">Link to this post</a>  </div></div>
