      <div class="msgContentFrame">IMO, they have to tune them that hard with entry level gear so by the time you get better gear (from heroics/raids/whatever) they'll get easier but still continue to be a challenge, and not like LK heroics that were too easy from the get-go. <br /> <br />I did hundreds of heroics at 70, and several hundred more at 80.  In the 70's you still scaled and they got easier with time, but initially I remember heroics being so ridiculous that certain groups refused to run them without a perfect makeup (H Shattered Halls comes to mind), by the time TBC was coming to a close, normal groups without cc were doing that instance without problems. At 80 I was scared to do my first heroics, remembering what 70 was like, when I got into one and realized it was barely a step up from normal I was disappointed.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Azjol-Nerub&amp;cn=Wheatle" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Azjol-Nerub&amp;cn=Wheatle">WoW Armory ~ Wheatle ~ Azjol-Nerub</a> <br /> <br />FFXIV | Hyur â™€ | Snow Board | 10 Pug | 12 Phys <br /> <br />&quot;I'm gonna get nice and drunk, then play video games until my eyes bleed.&quot; Charlie  (It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia)</div></div>
